Page 134 - A method defined in a class C should only call:
                            - Its parameters;
                            - Other instances methods in C;
                            - Methods in objects that it creates;

Page 134 - Don't chain call methods 
                -> amount = customers.orders.last().totals().amount (chain call)

Page 136 - Global data produces coupling and make the code more rigid, one change on the global may break everything.

Page 136 PP - Wrap resources behind code that you control (DB, Service API, File System, ...).

+ Code should only deal with things it directly know about.
